## Operating Systems

- Kali Linux 2025.3 (Attack / security testing)
- Windows 10 22H2 (Target / user simulation)
- Ubuntu 24.04 LTS (Server / networking support)

---

## Lab Design Approach

- Build isolated lab environments using virtual machines  
- Simulate real-world scenarios (attack, monitor, defend)  
- Focus on practical execution over theoretical learning  
- Maintain structured documentation for all activities  

---

## Workflow

1. Setup environment  
2. Execute task or experiment  
3. Capture outputs (logs, screenshots)  
4. Document findings  
5. Store results in repository  

---

## Purpose

To develop hands-on technical skills and convert them into structured, resume-ready projects.

